# Node Selector
- we can select a node on which our pod can be scheduled. It can be done with the help of labels

1. update the node with label
kubectl label no rahul-aio-control-plane size=Large

2. create a pod with the label
kubectl run nginx-label --image=nginx --labels=size=Large -n ckad

> Match with node name
...
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx
spec:
  nodeName: foo-node # schedule pod to specific node
  containers:
  - name: nginx-node-affinity
    image: nginx
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
...

# Node Affinity
- we can check the matching label if present on node, then only schedule else skip
> key in value
...
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx
spec:
  affinity:
    nodeAffinity:
      requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
        nodeSelectorTerms:
        - matchExpressions:
          - key: size
            operator: In
            values:
            - small            
  containers:
  - name: nginx-node-affinity
    image: nginx
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
...

> key exists
...
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx
spec:
  affinity:
    nodeAffinity:
      requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
        nodeSelectorTerms:
        - matchExpressions:
          - key: size
            operator: Exists        
  containers:
  - name: nginx-node-affinity
    image: nginx
    imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
...

> Preferred Execution
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: with-affinity-anti-affinity
spec:
  affinity:
    nodeAffinity:
      preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
      - weight: 1
        preference:
          matchExpressions:
          - key: label-1
            operator: In
            values:
            - key-1
      - weight: 50
        preference:
          matchExpressions:
          - key: label-2
            operator: In
            values:
            - key-2
  containers:
  - name: with-node-affinity
    image: registry.k8s.io/pause:2.0
---


Note: Dont try this on single base node
